item.title: CVE-2023-27989|2024-08-02T12:23:30.829Z -- zyxel -- nr7101%20firmware
item.description: A buffer overflow vulnerability in the CGI program of the Zyxel NR7101 firmware versions prior to V1.00(ABUV.8)C0 could allow a remote authenticated attacker to cause denial of service (DoS) conditions by sending a crafted HTTP request to a vulnerable device.
